{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bfc2bb56-3cc4-4f17-ac6d-e217b4bbb9f5","content":"If you need per-test setup logging, move that logic to a `[TestInitialize]` method where `TestContext.TestName` is still valid:\n\n```csharp\n[TestInitialize]\npublic void TestInit()\n{\n    var testName = TestContext.TestName; // works fine here\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Other v4 things to watch out for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Package** | `MSTest` (single package) replaces the old trio of `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` + `MSTest.Analyzers` |\n| **`[ClassInitialize]`/`[AssemblyInitialize]`** | `TestContext` is now scoped correctly — no test-specific properties (`TestName`, `TestResultsDirectory` per-test, etc.) |\n| **Analyzers** | New analyzers ship by default and may surface new warnings/errors |\n| **Timeout** | `[Timeout]` now applies to the test method only (not including `[TestInitialize]`/`[TestCleanup]`) |\n| **Parallel execution** | Defaults may differ — review `[Parallelize]` settings if you see new race conditions |\n| **`Assert.Inconclusive`** | Now correctly reported (previously could be swallowed in some runners) |\n\nYour project file already uses the unified `MSTest` v4.1.0 package, which is correct.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"33c12b36-896f-4a35-a860-1cc69010391b","outputTokens":344,"requestId":"5C20:3CEFF5:3FEB91:510149:69F56526"},"id":"1d8f3e61-2455-477f-a2ec-993c6fecb737","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:45:04.445Z","parentId":"fe40f472-4dad-4ccc-9fcf-8ca61283b957"}
